ABUJA – The National Association of Nigerian Students (NANS), the Ogun state chapter and the National Association of Ogun State Students (NAOSS) have lamented the set of lawmakers representing the state at the National Assembly, describing them as the worst in the history of the state. Besides, the student body also accused them of working against the incumbent state governor, Prince Dapo Abiodun and resolved to henceforth reject Federal lawmakers who are not living up to the expectations of the people of the state. NANS urged political parties to desist from fielding “passive” and “underperforming” candidates to represent the people of the state, particularly at the Federal level. -Advertisement- They bemoaned their fate, in a statement jointly signed by the chairman of NANS, Ogun JCC, Comrade Kehinde Damilola Simeon and the National President of NAOSS, Comrade Oluwagbemileke Ogunrombi and made available to Daily Independent on Sunday. The students’ body emphasized the people of Ogun State deserve better representatives who will contribute to the socio-economic development of the state, saying on the contrary the Senators representing the three Senatorial Districts of the state have performed below expectation. “Ogun State has had the worst set of lawmakers at the National Assembly who have been working against the state governor, Prince Dapo Abiodun. Ogun people deserve better representatives. We don’t want benchwarmers; we don’t want lawmakers that won’t facilitate developmental projects for the state. “It is unfortunate that besides being the worst set of Federal lawmakers at the National Assembly. All the three Senators representing the state have failed to live up to the expectations of the people.”